      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOYA DESTROYER (1) flew home from the back of the pack fresh over 1200m, being just 1.4L off the winner as the race favourite. The form out of that race has worked out well and this shapes as a suitable event on the back of that effort. Ticks plenty of boxes here and looks the one to beat. NICKELPLAY (5) stuck on well first-up at Bunbury over this distance, beaten 2.8L. Chris Parnham hops in the saddle now and she should get every chance off the inside draw. Hasn't won for a while but the fresh run suggested she's right on the cusp. COME ON EMMA (4) is racing well without winning this time in, sitting on the speed and ending up 1.6L off the winner last time out. Riordan remains in the saddle and she should be prominent from the draw. Can be in this for a long way. EXTREME LOVE (2) will be fitter for a trial coming into this and she can be thereabouts on resumption. ZORBRIST (3) won't be far away.",
